Souffle Grand Marnier, Les Petit Fours- is is generally recognized that the Arabs and Chinese knew the art of making iced sweets, especially water ices. It was the Chinese who taught the art of ice cream making to the Indians, the Persians and the Arabs. Ice cream and water ices were introduced into France about the year 1660 by a Sicilian named Francisco Procopio. Under the Second Empire, the first coupes, mousses and parfaits were made. The name Petits Four, according to Careme, comes from the fact that they are baked  in a slow oven after the big cakes have been baked, and the temperature of the oven has gone down considerably.

TIO PEPE SHERRY- Schieffelin & Co.-  Literally translated "Uncle Joe" is named after one of the older members of the Gonzalez family, whose favorite it was. Tio Pepe is considered the ultimate in Dry Sherry, being extremely dry and delicate. It is the standard by which all Dry Sherries ave been judged throughout the world for generations. Today, Gonzalez, Byass is known the world over as one of Spain's finest Sherries. Gonzales, Byass are the largest vineyard owners in Jerez, with over 1,000 acres of the finest Sherry producing vineyards. A minimum of 30,000 butts of selected Sherry is kept maturing in the Soleras of the firm's bodegas or warehouses. The company is 130 years old, having been founded by Don Manuel and Maria Gonzales.

Patrons- Don't Hurry Your Orders- Especially if it is cooked to order. Be patient, give it sufficient time to cook properly. Our sole aim is to please you. We have the goods and take pleasure in preparing and serving you satisfactorily, as it is your continued patronage we are seeking. Should you insist having your order hurried, that can be easily done, though it is a foolish move on your part. Bear in mind every man takes pride in his occupation. He is bent on turning out nice work, likewise a cook. It is quite aggravating to be compelled to do what he knows is wrong. To hurry an order it must be placed close to the fire and forced. Result, scorched on outside, raw inside, naturally emitting a burnt "gassy" taste, spoiling your meal entirely, making you feel out of sorts and you leave with a vowed intention of never returning again. - Choice goods abused, proprietor must suffer, though the fault is all your own.
